=My Calorie Boy=

15
00:01:37,940 --> 00:01:40,960
=Episode 30=
(Will the Dessert Turn into an Oasis?)

16
00:01:43,070 --> 00:01:45,130
(Happy graduation!)

17
00:01:45,805 --> 00:01:47,046
What... What did you say?

18
00:01:50,566 --> 00:01:52,126
I can't hear you.

19
00:01:52,566 --> 00:01:53,326
Shut up!

20
00:01:53,805 --> 00:01:55,445
Shut up! I can't hear him.

21
00:01:59,486 --> 00:02:01,126
I can't hear you.

22
00:02:08,766 --> 00:02:09,965
I can't hear you.

23
00:02:13,286 --> 00:02:14,486
I can't hear you.

24
00:02:25,420 --> 00:02:26,690
(Madam Wang Jiaren)

25
00:02:34,845 --> 00:02:35,486
Hey. Mom.

26
00:02:35,685 --> 00:02:36,926
Are you still sleeping?

27
00:02:38,486 --> 00:02:39,965
No. I'm making breakfast now.

28
00:02:40,206 --> 00:02:40,926
Liar.

29
00:02:41,405 --> 00:02:42,685
I could tell that you just woke up
by listening to your voice.

30
00:02:42,685 --> 00:02:43,405
Exactly.

31
00:02:44,365 --> 00:02:45,206
Anything else?

32
00:02:45,606 --> 00:02:46,206
Of course.

33
00:02:46,525 --> 00:02:47,525
I'm here to wake you up.

34
00:02:47,845 --> 00:02:48,805
If it wasn't for me,
would you even wake up by now?

35
00:02:49,286 --> 00:02:50,645
I told you the alarm clock
would wake me up.

36
00:02:50,886 --> 00:02:52,125
I didn't need you to wake me up.

37
00:02:52,365 --> 00:02:53,565
You have to
take your breakfast, all right?

38
00:02:53,886 --> 00:02:55,166
You can't go to work
with an empty stomach.

39
00:02:55,166 --> 00:02:55,965
That's right.

40
00:02:57,046 --> 00:02:58,046
Fine. I got it.

41
00:02:58,085 --> 00:02:58,766
Wait a minute.

42
00:02:58,766 --> 00:02:59,446
Your dad wants to talk to you.

43
00:02:59,685 --> 00:03:00,326
Mom.

44
00:03:00,525 --> 00:03:01,926
I'm running late.

45
00:03:02,525 --> 00:03:04,166
Fine. I've got to go.

46
00:03:04,405 --> 00:03:06,006
Don't wake me up tomorrow!

47
00:03:06,926 --> 00:03:07,645
Hey?

48
00:03:37,726 --> 00:03:38,805
Where's my computer?

49
00:03:46,326 --> 00:03:46,685
Hey.

50
00:03:46,886 --> 00:03:47,565
I would like to make a police report.

51
00:03:53,286 --> 00:03:53,886
Don't be scared.

52
00:03:54,326 --> 00:03:55,006
Take your time
and tell us what happened.

53
00:03:56,565 --> 00:03:57,446
I'm not scared.

54
00:03:57,805 --> 00:03:58,726
I'm just angry.

55
00:03:59,446 --> 00:04:00,286
I spent half a month working on this,

56
00:04:00,525 --> 00:04:02,125
and now all my effort is gone.

57
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:05,480
(Police Report)

58
00:04:07,085 --> 00:04:08,046
Are you Xu Jingjing?

59
00:04:09,326 --> 00:04:10,365
Are you Xu Jingjing too?

60
00:04:10,965 --> 00:04:11,805
I'm not.

61
00:04:14,006 --> 00:04:15,845
Do you work at a design studio?

62
00:04:16,325 --> 00:04:17,685
Are you a designer?

63
00:04:18,685 --> 00:04:19,205
I'm not.

64
00:04:19,486 --> 00:04:20,565
I'm just an assistant designer.

65
00:04:23,166 --> 00:04:24,646
Did you rent this place?

66
00:04:25,526 --> 00:04:26,805
I live quite far from the office,

67
00:04:27,166 --> 00:04:28,086
so I rented a unit

68
00:04:28,166 --> 00:04:29,486
near my workplace.

69
00:04:30,325 --> 00:04:31,205
Can you tell me

70
00:04:31,406 --> 00:04:32,685
what did you lose?

71
00:04:33,166 --> 00:04:33,646
Of course.

72
00:04:35,365 --> 00:04:36,205
My tablet

73
00:04:36,685 --> 00:04:37,606
and my computer.

74
00:04:38,046 --> 00:04:38,606
I won't be able to work

75
00:04:38,726 --> 00:04:39,565
without these two items.

76
00:04:39,926 --> 00:04:40,606
Also...

77
00:04:41,286 --> 00:04:42,166
My bag too.

78
00:04:43,205 --> 00:04:44,046
It's a designer bag.

79
00:04:44,646 --> 00:04:45,805
It's very precious

80
00:04:45,805 --> 00:04:46,805
for me.

81
00:04:51,005 --> 00:04:51,966
Okay. I got it.

82
00:04:52,565 --> 00:04:53,286
We'll inform you right away

83
00:04:53,325 --> 00:04:54,526
if we find anything.

84
00:04:55,166 --> 00:04:55,846
Thank you so much.

85
00:04:56,325 --> 00:04:57,046
Don't worry.

86
00:05:24,365 --> 00:05:24,966
Can I have a pancake?

87
00:05:25,445 --> 00:05:26,445
Extra crispy, with sausage and egg.

88
00:05:26,765 --> 00:05:27,406
Sure.

89
00:05:28,685 --> 00:05:29,885
Madam, you haven't changed a bit.

90
00:05:30,286 --> 00:05:31,125
You still look as young as before.

91
00:05:33,005 --> 00:05:33,846
And you are...

92
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:35,245
I was a student of Yuming.

93
00:05:36,325 --> 00:05:37,685
Yuming's student? Have a seat.

94
00:05:37,926 --> 00:05:39,005
Let me give you an extra egg.

95
00:05:39,406 --> 00:05:40,125
Thanks, Madam.

96
00:05:44,885 --> 00:05:46,125
Can I copy your answers, please?

97
00:05:46,286 --> 00:05:47,606
You have nothing to lose.

98
00:05:47,885 --> 00:05:48,606
I just don't get it.

99
00:05:48,805 --> 00:05:49,445
Why can't you

100
00:05:49,526 --> 00:05:50,365
do your own homework?

101
00:05:51,086 --> 00:05:52,646
I wouldn't need to copy yours
if I know how to do it.

102
00:05:52,966 --> 00:05:53,646
I can teach you.

103
00:05:53,966 --> 00:05:54,726
I just don't understand any of them.

104
00:05:55,046 --> 00:05:56,646
If so, why do you even
bother coming to school?

105
00:05:57,445 --> 00:05:58,286
Kang Jiawei!

106
00:06:27,620 --> 00:06:29,320
(Mom)

107
00:06:35,526 --> 00:06:36,245
Hey. Mom.

108
00:06:37,646 --> 00:06:39,005
I arrived early. I'm eating now.

109
00:06:41,125 --> 00:06:41,606
I'll meet up

110
00:06:41,726 --> 00:06:42,565
with the designer later.

111
00:06:43,046 --> 00:06:44,245
We'll talk about
the makeover of the house.

112
00:06:49,685 --> 00:06:50,445
Good morning.

113
00:06:50,685 --> 00:06:51,445
Good morning.

114
00:06:55,245 --> 00:06:55,885
Sorry, Mr. Wei.

115
00:06:56,445 --> 00:06:57,005
I'm here.

116
00:06:57,005 --> 00:06:57,966
Jingjing, have a seat.

117
00:06:59,205 --> 00:07:00,205
How's it going?

118
00:07:00,726 --> 00:07:01,365
It's fine.

119
00:07:01,365 --> 00:07:02,565
I'm just really mad.

120
00:07:03,046 --> 00:07:03,765
If I ever

121
00:07:03,846 --> 00:07:04,486
run into the thief,

122
00:07:04,685 --> 00:07:05,486
I'll definitely make him pay for it.

123
00:07:05,885 --> 00:07:06,646
Stop talking big.

124
00:07:06,685 --> 00:07:07,526
You're a young lady,

125
00:07:07,646 --> 00:07:08,926
so stop acting tough.

126
00:07:09,685 --> 00:07:10,445
Most importantly,

127
00:07:11,565 --> 00:07:13,125
I lost

128
00:07:13,166 --> 00:07:13,846
my tablet and computer.

129
00:07:16,286 --> 00:07:16,966
You can borrow mine.

130
00:07:18,406 --> 00:07:19,406
Buy a new one later in the afternoon,

131
00:07:19,726 --> 00:07:20,526
and submit the claim to me later.

132
00:07:22,325 --> 00:07:23,726
You're being too nice.

133
00:07:23,966 --> 00:07:24,646
All right. Don't get too touched.

134
00:07:24,846 --> 00:07:25,646
Get ready in the meeting room now.

135
00:07:25,846 --> 00:07:26,486
Our client will arrive soon.

136
00:07:26,685 --> 00:07:27,166
Sure.

137
00:07:31,805 --> 00:07:32,606
Jingjing.

138
00:07:33,606 --> 00:07:34,926
It's been a while
since you started working with me.

139
00:07:35,086 --> 00:07:35,885
I want to let you try

140
00:07:36,966 --> 00:07:38,046
handling this project on your own.

141
00:07:38,526 --> 00:07:39,685
Really, Mr. Wei?

142
00:07:40,245 --> 00:07:41,685
Am I going to be
a full-fledged designer soon?

143
00:07:42,005 --> 00:07:42,445
You should understand

144
00:07:42,606 --> 00:07:43,565
the project first.

145
00:07:44,286 --> 00:07:45,046
The previous owner of this place

146
00:07:45,606 --> 00:07:46,526
was a designer too.

147
00:07:46,765 --> 00:07:47,726
He left us with some suggestions.

148
00:07:48,125 --> 00:07:49,005
Our client hopes

149
00:07:49,726 --> 00:07:50,365
that we can do our best

150
00:07:50,606 --> 00:07:51,445
to reserve these ideas.

151
00:07:52,086 --> 00:07:53,646
It won't be fun if I don't get
to use my original design.

152
00:07:56,325 --> 00:07:57,046
Mr. Kang, you're here.

153
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:02,480
(Meeting Room)

154
00:08:05,526 --> 00:08:06,205
Hello.

155
00:08:07,005 --> 00:08:07,445
Hi.

156
00:08:07,606 --> 00:08:08,205
You're Mr. Wei, right?

157
00:08:08,365 --> 00:08:08,805
Yes.

158
00:08:09,005 --> 00:08:09,846
We spoke on the phone before.

159
00:08:17,046 --> 00:08:17,526
Jingjing.

160
00:08:17,885 --> 00:08:18,486
Jingjing.

161
00:08:19,445 --> 00:08:20,365
Come here.

162
00:08:22,445 --> 00:08:23,166
I spoke to you

163
00:08:23,325 --> 00:08:24,125
about her before.

164
00:08:24,286 --> 00:08:24,765
The youngest designer

165
00:08:24,846 --> 00:08:25,486
in our office.

166
00:08:25,646 --> 00:08:26,245
Xu Jingjing.

167
00:08:26,565 --> 00:08:27,286
She's very talented.

168
00:08:29,526 --> 00:08:30,166
Hello.

169
00:08:30,966 --> 00:08:31,765
I've heard a lot about you.

170
00:08:39,805 --> 00:08:40,485
Excuse me.

171
00:08:44,685 --> 00:08:45,845
Sorry about that.

172
00:08:51,205 --> 00:08:52,205
Wake up, Xu Jingjing.

173
00:08:52,445 --> 00:08:53,286
Wake up!

174
00:08:54,766 --> 00:08:55,565
Why are you still dreaming?

175
00:09:00,126 --> 00:09:00,965
It's not a dream.

176
00:09:07,926 --> 00:09:08,965
Xu Jingjing.

177
00:09:10,406 --> 00:09:11,805
Look at you.

178
00:09:12,886 --> 00:09:14,366
What are you wearing?

179
00:09:14,605 --> 00:09:16,085
Why do you look like
an elementary school student?

180
00:09:21,406 --> 00:09:22,445
Also,

181
00:09:22,605 --> 00:09:25,046
why didn't you wash your hair?

182
00:09:29,965 --> 00:09:31,166
Wait a minute.

183
00:09:31,845 --> 00:09:33,766
Why do you care

184
00:09:33,805 --> 00:09:34,926
how you appear to him?

185
00:09:35,205 --> 00:09:35,965
What's so special about him?

186
00:09:35,965 --> 00:09:36,926
He's just another client, right?

187
00:09:37,646 --> 00:09:38,646
Just like any other client.

188
00:09:44,366 --> 00:09:44,965
Amy.

189
00:09:45,845 --> 00:09:47,085
Do you have eyebrow pencils, mascara,

190
00:09:47,965 --> 00:09:49,886
lipstick, and foundation

191
00:09:49,886 --> 00:09:51,246
in your bag?

192
00:09:51,406 --> 00:09:52,286
I do. What's wrong?

193
00:09:52,526 --> 00:09:53,366
That's great.

194
00:10:01,246 --> 00:10:01,805
Mr. Kang.

195
00:10:02,006 --> 00:10:02,766
Sorry.

196
00:10:03,406 --> 00:10:04,886
Xu was facing some issues at home today.

197
00:10:05,526 --> 00:10:06,805
I guess she has gone home
to settle the issue.

198
00:10:07,126 --> 00:10:08,166
Did something happen?

199
00:10:09,006 --> 00:10:09,766
What happened? Is it bad?

200
00:10:10,006 --> 00:10:10,605
It's quite bad.

201
00:10:11,006 --> 00:10:12,286
Her place was broken into.

202
00:10:12,526 --> 00:10:13,246
Sorry.

203
00:10:13,286 --> 00:10:14,046
Sorry to have kept you waiting.

204
00:10:14,246 --> 00:10:15,006
Let's proceed.

205
00:10:16,366 --> 00:10:17,406
We were waiting for you.

206
00:10:19,046 --> 00:10:19,926
Mr. Kang.

207
00:10:21,126 --> 00:10:21,685
I have gone through

208
00:10:21,845 --> 00:10:22,526
all the basic information
regarding your project.

209
00:10:22,685 --> 00:10:23,965
I heard

210
00:10:24,006 --> 00:10:24,646
that you had some special requests too.

211
00:10:24,805 --> 00:10:25,565
Your house was broken into?

212
00:10:26,565 --> 00:10:27,246
Is it bad?

213
00:10:28,166 --> 00:10:28,805
Why are you living alone now?

214
00:10:29,006 --> 00:10:29,565
Where do you live?

215
00:10:29,805 --> 00:10:30,685
Why is the security so bad?

216
00:10:31,046 --> 00:10:31,845
These are my personal matters.

217
00:10:32,166 --> 00:10:32,886
We're now talking about

218
00:10:33,085 --> 00:10:33,725
the renovation of your place.

219
00:10:33,926 --> 00:10:34,926
Answer me now.

220
00:10:36,366 --> 00:10:37,006
I refuse to.

221
00:10:37,286 --> 00:10:37,805
Jingjing.

222
00:10:38,085 --> 00:10:39,366
Watch your words.

223
00:10:39,685 --> 00:10:40,445
Mr. Kang is our client.

224
00:10:40,646 --> 00:10:41,406
Xu Jingjing.

225
00:10:42,646 --> 00:10:43,445
I'm just concerned.

226
00:10:43,565 --> 00:10:44,406
I worry about you. Get it?

227
00:10:44,445 --> 00:10:45,126
I don't need you to worry about me.

228
00:10:45,126 --> 00:10:45,766
I didn't need it,

229
00:10:45,766 --> 00:10:46,766
and I won't need it now too.

230
00:10:53,605 --> 00:10:54,286
Excuse me.

231
00:10:54,725 --> 00:10:55,605
Are you friends?

232
00:10:55,766 --> 00:10:56,725
- Yes.
- No.

233
00:10:59,565 --> 00:11:00,565
Sorry, Mr. Wei.

234
00:11:01,445 --> 00:11:02,805
It seems like

235
00:11:02,845 --> 00:11:04,166
Mr. Kang is not here for business.

236
00:11:04,565 --> 00:11:05,286
Perhaps you can
continue with the discussion.

237
00:11:05,926 --> 00:11:06,805
I'll get back to work.

238
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:16,820
(Gao Zhan)

239
00:11:21,646 --> 00:11:23,205
What's happening?

240
00:11:24,886 --> 00:11:25,725
Hi. Gao Zhan.

241
00:12:27,685 --> 00:12:28,366
Dad.

242
00:12:32,286 --> 00:12:32,965
I'm home.

243
00:12:39,445 --> 00:12:39,965
Don't worry.

244
00:12:39,965 --> 00:12:40,805
I'm not running away from my mom.

245
00:12:44,766 --> 00:12:45,766
We've been quite amicable
with each other

246
00:12:45,766 --> 00:12:46,526
over the past few years.

247
00:12:55,166 --> 00:12:56,845
I've been able to maintain my weight.

248
00:12:58,046 --> 00:12:58,965
I'm not too chubby or too thin.

249
00:13:00,325 --> 00:13:01,886
I'm also 0.5cm taller than before.

250
00:13:05,766 --> 00:13:06,766
Career-wise...

251
00:13:08,605 --> 00:13:09,725
I'm planning to start a business
back in our home country.

252
00:13:11,325 --> 00:13:12,205
I'm going to venture
into the education industry.

253
00:13:13,646 --> 00:13:14,965
I guess that's what I'm good at.

254
00:13:19,845 --> 00:13:21,046
As for the rest...

255
00:13:29,406 --> 00:13:30,406
As for the rest,

256
00:13:33,085 --> 00:13:34,126
things aren't going too well.

257
00:13:50,526 --> 00:13:51,845
Qi is so good-looking.

258
00:13:52,805 --> 00:13:54,006
That was hilarious.

259
00:13:54,126 --> 00:13:54,845
Let's rewind

260
00:13:55,166 --> 00:13:56,366
and play it again.

261
00:14:01,646 --> 00:14:02,646
It's been so many years

262
00:14:02,805 --> 00:14:04,166
and we still laugh at stupid things.

263
00:14:04,685 --> 00:14:05,845
It's been so many years,

264
00:14:06,366 --> 00:14:07,246
and

265
00:14:07,605 --> 00:14:08,886
I still only have eyes for Qi.

266
00:14:09,166 --> 00:14:10,166
You're a director now.

267
00:14:10,526 --> 00:14:11,286
Back then, you were a fan.

268
00:14:11,366 --> 00:14:12,445
Now, you're the person
who makes them the stars.

269
00:14:12,965 --> 00:14:14,085
You held an art exhibition too.

270
00:14:14,485 --> 00:14:15,565
And it's soon going to be

271
00:14:16,126 --> 00:14:17,926
you and Dapeng's fourth anniversary.

272
00:14:18,485 --> 00:14:19,725
I'll ditch him sooner or later.

273
00:14:19,965 --> 00:14:21,565
He plays game day and night.

274
00:14:22,126 --> 00:14:23,246
Let's play it again.

275
00:14:24,646 --> 00:14:25,805
I met Kang Jiawei.

276
00:14:31,926 --> 00:14:32,646
I said...

277
00:14:33,286 --> 00:14:34,445
Kang Jiawei is back.

278
00:14:34,965 --> 00:14:36,006
He visited my office today

279
00:14:36,560 --> 00:14:37,641
and intended to hire me as his designer.

280
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:38,840
He wants me to
do a makeover for his room.

281
00:14:39,121 --> 00:14:40,041
Is he handsome now?

282
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:41,521
He looks decent.

283
00:14:41,881 --> 00:14:42,600
Did his weight rebound?

284
00:14:42,921 --> 00:14:43,440
No.

285
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:44,401
Does he have a girlfriend now?

286
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:46,200
